What is Git?

Git is a distributed version control system 

It tracks changes in any set of computer files

It is used for usually used for coordinating work among programmers who are collaboratively developing source code 

So when you'll be working on your 301 project as a team it will help you collaboratively work on source code together.
by keeping track of who made what changes and when.

Git allows you to maintain a local repository on your machine and a remote repository on git servers.


https://docs.github.com/en/get-started/getting-started-with-git/setting-your-username-in-git



